---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const transcript = {
  title: 'ACL Reconstruction Surgical Technique',
  subtitle: 'Three-Portal Technique performed by Kevin R. Stone, MD',
  category: 'Surgical Technique',
  duration: '4:30',
  relatedResearch: '/research/ligaments',
  relatedVideo: '/videos#surgical-techniques',
};
---

<Layout title={transcript.title + " - Transcript"}>
  <!-- Header -->
  <section class="bg-stone-900 text-white py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <a href="/transcripts" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-stone-400 hover:text-white text-sm mb-6 transition-colors">
        <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M15 19l-7-7 7-7"/>
        </svg>
        All Transcripts
      </a>
      
      <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
        <span class="text-xs px-3 py-1 bg-amber-500/20 text-amber-300 rounded-full">{transcript.category}</span>
        <span class="text-stone-400 text-sm">{transcript.duration}</span>
      </div>
      
      <h1 class="font-display text-display-sm md:text-display-md text-white mb-3">
        {transcript.title}
      </h1>
      <p class="text-lg text-stone-300">{transcript.subtitle}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Transcript Content -->
  <section class="py-12 md:py-16">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="prose prose-stone max-w-none">
        <div class="bg-stone-50 border-l-4 border-amber-500 p-6 mb-8 not-prose">
          <p class="text-sm text-stone-600">
            <strong class="text-stone-900">Video Overview:</strong> This video demonstrates Dr. Stone's 
            three-portal technique for ACL reconstruction using donor allograft tissue, including notch 
            preparation, tunnel placement, and graft fixation.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2 class="font-display text-xl text-stone-900 mb-4">Full Transcript</h2>
        
        <div class="space-y-6 text-stone-700 leading-relaxed">
          <p class="timestamp-text">
            <span class="timestamp">[00:05]</span>
            Our technique of ACL reconstruction involves what we call a three portal technique. After 
            arthroscopic treatment of other problems within the knee, such as treatment of articular 
            cartilage defects and torn meniscus cartilages, the ACL is approached by first cleaning 
            out the intercondylar notch.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            Taking care to obtain excellent visualization of the ACL insertion sites on the tibia and 
            on the femur wall. Notch plasty is performed only if necessary to improve visualization or 
            if there is a particularly tight intercondylar notch.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            Once the notch is cleared, a guide is passed from the anterior medial portal exiting 
            posterolaterally at the level of the iliotibial band. A small puncture wound is made over 
            the tip of the guide through the skin.
          </p>
          
          <p class="timestamp-text">
            <span class="timestamp">[01:15]</span>
            The rear entry guide is hooked onto the small puncture wound, and the tibial tunnel is then 
            drilled from outside-in. This technique permits excellent placement of the tibial tunnel at 
            the anatomic insertion site of the native ACL.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            The femoral tunnel is then drilled through the tibial tunnel, taking care to position the 
            tunnel at the anatomic femoral insertion site. Tunnel position is confirmed both 
            arthroscopically and with fluoroscopy.
          </p>
          
          <p class="timestamp-text">
            <span class="timestamp">[02:30]</span>
            The donor tendon graft—which has been sterilized and prepared—is then passed through the 
            tibial tunnel and into the femoral tunnel. We prefer to use allograft tissue to avoid 
            harvest damage to the patient's own tissues.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            The graft is secured on the femoral side first, typically with an interference screw or 
            suspensory fixation device. The knee is then cycled through a full range of motion to 
            pretension the graft.
          </p>
          
          <p class="timestamp-text">
            <span class="timestamp">[03:30]</span>
            Tibial fixation is then performed with the knee at approximately 20 degrees of flexion, 
            with an anterior drawer force applied to the tibia. This ensures appropriate tension in 
            the graft throughout the range of motion.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            Final stability testing confirms elimination of the pivot shift and anterior drawer. The 
            portals are closed, and the patient is placed in a hinged knee brace for the early 
            rehabilitation period.
          </p>
          
          <p>
            At the Stone Clinic in San Francisco, we treat athletes of all ages and in all sports and 
            have extensive experience rebuilding anterior cruciate ligaments to return patients to 
            active, stable knees.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Related Links -->
  <section class="py-12 bg-stone-50 border-t border-stone-200">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h3 class="font-display text-lg text-stone-900 mb-6">Related Content</h3>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <a href={transcript.relatedResearch} class="p-5 bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-sm hover:border-amber-400 transition-colors group">
          <span class="text-xs text-amber-600 uppercase tracking-wider">Research</span>
          <p class="font-display text-stone-900 group-hover:text-amber-600 transition-colors mt-1">Ligaments & Tendons Studies</p>
        </a>
        <a href={transcript.relatedVideo} class="p-5 bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-sm hover:border-amber-400 transition-colors group">
          <span class="text-xs text-amber-600 uppercase tracking-wider">Video</span>
          <p class="font-display text-stone-900 group-hover:text-amber-600 transition-colors mt-1">Watch Full Video</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .timestamp {
    @apply text-xs font-mono text-amber-600 bg-amber-50 px-2 py-0.5 rounded mr-2;
  }
</style>
